@Database CFG_ACCOUNTDEFAULTS

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.CFG - Config File"

  Description:

  The files in the directory "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults" are used by the
  account editor and the new user door to apply default account settings, based
  on access level, to an account.

  The files names can be "Level_<ACS>.CFG" or "<AccessName>.CFG" or they can have
  the same names as files in the ConfAcs directory.

  They are searched for in that order.  If none can be found an error will be
  logged to the log file specified by the setting @{"BBSGlobal/ErrorLogFile" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/BBSGlobal.Guide/ErrorLogFile}

  Think of these files as account templates!

  Also see the file @{"HBBS:Nodes/NodeList" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeList.Guide/Main}, which defines the AccessName and
  ConfAcs names.

  Options:

  TimeAllowed=<number>              @{" More... " link TimeAllowed}
  ChatAllowed=<number>              @{" More... " link ChatAllowed}
  CallsAllowed=<number>             @{" More... " link CallsAllowed}
  BytesAllowed=<number>             @{" More... " link BytesAllowed}
  UserType=<string>                 @{" More... " link UserType}
  LanguageNumber=<number>           @{" More... " link LanguageNumber}
  PreferredConf=<number>            @{" More... " link PreferredConf}
  LastConf=<number>                 @{" More... " link LastConf}
  BytesRatio=<number>               @{" More... " link BytesRatio}
  FilesRatio=<number>               @{" More... " link FilesRatio}
  FreeUploadBytes=<number>          @{" More... " link FreeUploadBytes}

@EndNode

@Node TimeAllowed "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/TimeAllowed - Config File"

  TimeAllowed=<number>

    E.G.

    TimeAllowed=60

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Sets the amount of time the user can be connected to the BBS for in each
    24 hour period.

    In minutes.

@EndNode

@Node ChatAllowed "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/ChatAllowed - Config File"

  ChatAllowed=<number>

    E.G.

    ChatAllowed=10

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Sets the amount of times the user can be chatting to another user while on-line
    in each 24 hour period.  (Including chatting to the sysop)

@EndNode

@Node CallsAllowed "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/CallsAllowed - Config File"

  CallsAllowed=<number>

    E.G.

    CallsAllowed=10

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Sets the amount of times the user can call the BBS in each 24 hour period

@EndNode

@Node BytesAllowed "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/BytesAllowed - Config File"

  BytesAllowed=<number>

    E.G.

    BytesAllowed=5000000 ; 5MB

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Sets the amount of bytes a user is to download in each 24 hour period, unless they
    upload as well.

@EndNode

@Node UserType "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/UserType - Config File"

  UserType=<string>

    Must be either "EXPERT" or "NORMAL"
    E.G.

    UserType=EXPERT

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Set's the user type for the user.

@EndNode

@Node LanguageNumber "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/LanguageNumber - Config File"

  LanguageNumber=<number>

    E.G.

    LanguageNumber=2

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Set's the language for the user to use, see @{"BBSGlobal/LanguageName_XX" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/BBSGlobal.Guide/LanguageName_XX}

@EndNode

@Node PreferredConf "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/PreferredConf - Config File"

  PreferredConf=<number>

    E.G.

    PreferredConf=4

    No Default, Need not be set.

    The conference a user wants to be in every time they call the BBS.

@EndNode

@Node LastConf "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/LastConf - Config File"

  LastConf=<number>

    E.G.

    LastConf=2

    No Default, Need not be set.

    The conference number that you wish the user to join when the next log-in to
    the BBS.

@EndNode

@Node BytesRatio "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/BytesRatio - Config File"

  BytesRatio=<number>

    E.G.

    BytesRatio=3

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Specifies the download:upload ratio, i.e. BytesRatio:1

    If you set this to 3, the user can download 3 bytes for every 1 byte uploaded.

    So if the user has uploaded 3MB, they can download 9MB

@EndNode

@Node FilesRatio "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/FilesRatio - Config File"

  FilesRatio=<number>

    E.G.

    FilesRatio=5

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Specifies the download:upload ratio, i.e. FilesRatio:1

    If you set this to 3, the user can download 3 files for every 1 file uploaded.

@EndNode

@Node FreeUploadBytes "HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/#?.cfg/FreeUploadBytes - Config File"

  FreeUploadBytes=<number>

    E.G.

    FreeUploadBytes=3000000 ; 3MB

    No Default, Need not be set.

    Added to the user's upload bytes number, ONLY if the user's upload bytes
    is zero (0)

@EndNode
